'''Kojo Peprah Oppong ''' (born 4 June 2004) is a French-Ghanaian<ref>{{Cite web |last=Demba |first=Varore |date=24 April 2024 |title=Kojo Peprah Oppong : "Depuis tout petit, j'ai baigné dans la culture ghanéenne" - Football |url=https://sportnewsafrica.com/news-football/montpellier-modibo-sagnan-depuis-tout-petit-jai-baigne-dans-la-culture-malienne/ |access-date=7 August 2025 |website=Sport News Africa |language=fr-FR}}</ref> professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[OGC Nice|Nice]] and the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]].

==Early life==
Peprah Oppong was born on 4 June 2004 in [[Accra]], Ghana. The son of Cecilia and Joseph, he has a sister. He holds [[French nationality]] from his mother.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nt.se/story-sport/fotboll/artikel/smog-ut-pa-morgnarna-i-jakt-pa-drommen-mamma-hjalpte-mig/jvdg0y1j|title=Han smög ut på morgnarna – i jakt på drömmen: "Mamma hjälpte mig"|trans-title=He sneaked out in the mornings – in pursuit of the dream: "Mom helped me"|language=sv|publisher=[[Norrköpings Tidningar]]|date=25 March 2025|access-date=7 August 2025}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Demba |first=Varore |date=24 April 2024 |title=Kojo Peprah Oppong : "Depuis tout petit, j'ai baigné dans la culture ghanéenne" - Football |url=https://sportnewsafrica.com/news-football/montpellier-modibo-sagnan-depuis-tout-petit-jai-baigne-dans-la-culture-malienne/ |access-date=7 August 2025 |website=Sport News Africa |language=fr-FR}}</ref>

==Club career==
Peprah Oppong started his career with Ghanaian side [[Attram De Visser Soccer Academy|Attram De Visser]]. Following his stint there, he signed for Swedish side [[IFK Norrköping]] in 2023, where he made sixteen league appearances and scored zero goals.

During the summer of the same year, he was sent on loan to Swedish side [[GIF Sundsvall]], where he made thirty-eight league appearances and scored zero goals. Ahead of the [[2025–26 Ligue 1|2025–26 season]], he signed for French [[Ligue 1]] side [[OGC Nice|Nice]].<ref>{{Soccerway|888675}}</ref>

==International career==
In October 2025, Peprah Oppong earned his maiden invitation to the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana senior national team]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Taiwo |first=Taiye |title=Exclusive: OGC Nice Defender Kojo Peprah Oppong Set for Maiden Ghana Call-Up |url=https://www.sportsboom.com/football/exclusive-ogc-nice-defender-oppong-set-for-maiden-ghana-callup/ |access-date=18 October 2025 |website=SportsBoom}}</ref> He made his international debut in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification|2026 FIFA World Cup qualifier]] against [[Comoros national football team|Comoros]] at the [[Accra Sports Stadium]] on 12 October 2025.

==Style of play==
Peprah Oppong plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] and is right-footed. French news website wrote in 2025 that he is "a solid defender, strong on the man and very lively... a versatile central defender... can play on either the right or left flank".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://quatretroistrois.fr/qui-est-kojo-peprah-oppong-5eme-recrue-de-logc-nice/|title=Qui est Kojo Peprah Oppong, 5ème recrue de l’OGC Nice?|trans-title=Who is Kojo Peprah Oppong, OGC Nice's 5th signing?|language=fr|publisher=QuatreTroisTrois|date=23 July 2025|access-date=7 August 2025}}</ref>

